{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QVTYEdJEnKuUBBMjJ3GGC2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 5.2: Flow Execution — Loop Blocks\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want loop: blocks to repeat until pass or circuit breaker,\n9\tso that retry cycles are automatic with evaluator findings injected into retry prompts.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `workflow-engine.ts` encounters a `loop:` block (e.g., `loop: [retry, verify]`) in the flow array\n14\t   **When** it processes the flow step\n15\t   **Then** it iterates through the loop's task list sequentially, repeating the entire loop block until a termination condition is met\n16\t   **And** replaces the current \"skip with warning\" behavior from story 5-1\n17\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t2. **Given** the loop block contains `[retry, verify]` and the verify task produces an `EvaluatorVerdict`\n20\t   **When** the verdict has `verdict: 'pass'` (all ACs passed)\n21\t   **Then** the loop terminates immediately after that verify step\n22\t   **And** workflow state records the final passing iteration\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** the loop block is iterating\n26\t   **When** `state.iteration` reaches a configurable `maxIterations` limit (default: 5)\n27\t   **Then** the loop terminates\n28\t   **And** workflow state phase is set to `\"max-iterations\"`\n29\t   **And** the engine returns `EngineResult` with `success: false`\n30\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** the loop block is iterating and a circuit breaker module is available\n33\t   **When** `circuit_breaker.triggered` becomes `true` in workflow state\n34\t   **Then** the loop terminates\n35\t   **And** workflow state phase is set to `\"circuit-breaker\"`\n36\t   **And** the engine returns `EngineResult` with `success: false`\n37\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t5. **Given** a verify task produces an `EvaluatorVerdict` with per-AC findings\n40\t   **When** the retry task runs in the next loop iteration\n41\t   **Then** the retry prompt includes the evaluator's findings: failed AC descriptions, status, evidence, and reasoning\n42\t   **And** only stories/issues flagged as failed by the evaluator are retried (not all work items)\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t6. **Given** a verify task completes\n46\t   **When** its `DispatchResult.output` is parsed\n47\t   **Then** the engine attempts to parse it as an `EvaluatorVerdict` JSON object\n48\t   **And** if parsing succeeds, records the score in `state.evaluator_scores`\n49\t   **And** if parsing fails, records an all-UNKNOWN score with `{ passed: 0, failed: 0, unknown: total, total }` where total is the number of work items\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t7. **Given** the loop block increments `state.iteration` each time it starts a new loop pass\n53\t   **When** each loop pass completes (whether via retry+verify or just verify)\n54\t   **Then** `state.iteration` is incremented by 1 before the next pass\n55\t   **And** the updated iteration is persisted to disk via `writeWorkflowState()`\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t8. **Given** the engine is executing a loop block\n59\t   **When** a `DispatchError` with a halt-worthy code (`RATE_LIMIT`, `NETWORK`, `SDK_INIT`) occurs\n60\t   **Then** the loop terminates immediately\n61\t   **And** the error is recorded in state and in `EngineResult.errors`\n62\t   **And** behavior is consistent with the existing error handling from story 5-1\n63\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t9. **Given** unit tests for the loop block execution\n66\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n67\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for loop-related code paths covering: loop termination on pass, loop termination on max iterations, loop termination on circuit breaker, finding injection into retry prompt, failed-story-only retry filtering, verdict parsing success, verdict parsing failure, iteration increment and persistence, halt error during loop, and empty loop block\n68\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t10. **Given** the existing sequential flow tests from story 5-1\n71\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed after loop block implementation\n72\t    **Then** all existing workflow-engine tests continue to pass with zero regressions\n73\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n74\t\n75\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n76\t\n77\t- [ ] Task 1: Define loop execution interfaces and types (AC: #1, #6)\n78\t  - [ ] Add `EvaluatorVerdict` interface to `workflow-engine.ts` (matching AD5 from architecture): `{ verdict: 'pass' | 'fail'; score: { passed, failed, unknown, total }; findings: Array<{ ac, description, status, evidence }> }`\n79\t  - [ ] Add `LoopConfig` interface: `{ maxIterations: number }` with default 5\n80\t  - [ ] Add `maxIterations` to `EngineConfig` as optional field (default: 5)\n81\t  - [ ] Add `parseVerdict(output: string): EvaluatorVerdict | null` function — attempts JSON.parse, returns null on failure\n82\t\n83\t- [ ] Task 2: Implement verdict parsing and score recording (AC: #6)\n84\t  - [ ] Implement `parseVerdict(output: string): EvaluatorVerdict | null`\n85\t  - [ ] Validate parsed JSON has required fields (`verdict`, `score`, `findings`)\n86\t  - [ ] On parse success: create `EvaluatorScore` from verdict.score and append to `state.evaluator_scores`\n87\t  - [ ] On parse failure: create all-UNKNOWN `EvaluatorScore` and append to `state.evaluator_scores`\n88\t  - [ ] Write updated state to disk after recording score\n89\t\n90\t- [ ] Task 3: Implement finding injection for retry prompts (AC: #5)\n91\t  - [ ] Implement `buildRetryPrompt(storyKey: string, findings: EvaluatorVerdict['findings']): string`\n92\t  - [ ] Filter findings to only those with `status: 'fail'` or `status: 'unknown'`\n93\t  - [ ] Format: include AC number, description, status, evidence.reasoning for each failed finding\n94\t  - [ ] Prepend to the existing prompt: `\"Retry story {storyKey}. Previous evaluator findings:\\n{formattedFindings}\"`\n95\t\n96\t- [ ] Task 4: Implement failed-story filtering (AC: #5)\n97\t  - [ ] After verdict parse, determine which work items failed\n98\t  - [ ] For per-story retry tasks: dispatch only for failed work items (not all)\n99\t  - [ ] If verdict parse failed (null), retry all work items (conservative fallback)\n100\t  - [ ] Track failed items as a set derived from verdict findings\n101\t\n102\t- [ ] Task 5: Implement loop block execution (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #7, #8)\n103\t  - [ ] Replace the `isLoopBlock` skip logic in `executeWorkflow()` with actual loop execution\n104\t  - [ ] Implement `executeLoopBlock(loopBlock: LoopBlock, state: WorkflowState, config: EngineConfig, workItems: WorkItem[]): Promise<{ state: WorkflowState; errors: EngineError[]; tasksCompleted: number; halted: boolean }>`\n105\t  - [ ] Loop logic:\n106\t    1. Increment `state.iteration`\n107\t    2. For each task in `loopBlock.loop`:\n108\t       - Look up task and agent definition (same as sequential)\n109\t       - If task is `per-story` and we have a previous verdict: dispatch only for failed items, with findings injected\n110\t       - If task is `per-story` and no verdict yet: dispatch for all items\n111\t       - If task is `per-run`: dispatch once (e.g., verify)\n112\t       - After a per-run dispatch: attempt to parse verdict from `DispatchResult.output`\n113\t       - Record score in state\n114\t    3. Check termination: verdict.verdict === 'pass' → terminate (success)\n115\t    4. Check termination: `state.iteration >= maxIterations` → terminate (max-iterations)\n116\t    5. Check termination: `state.circuit_breaker.triggered` → terminate (circuit-breaker)\n117\t    6. Otherwise: repeat from step 1\n118\t  - [ ] Handle `DispatchError` with halt codes: terminate loop, propagate error\n119\t  - [ ] Update `executeWorkflow()` to call `executeLoopBlock()` instead of skipping\n120\t\n121\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n122\t  - [ ] Add tests to `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` in a new `describe('loop block execution')` section\n123\t  - [ ] Test: loop terminates when verdict is 'pass'\n124\t  - [ ] Test: loop terminates when maxIterations reached\n125\t  - [ ] Test: loop terminates when circuit_breaker.triggered is true\n126\t  - [ ] Test: findings injected into retry prompt for failed stories\n127\t  - [ ] Test: only failed stories retried (not all work items)\n128\t  - [ ] Test: verdict parsed from DispatchResult.output\n129\t  - [ ] Test: invalid verdict JSON produces all-UNKNOWN score\n130\t  - [ ] Test: iteration incremented and persisted each loop pass\n131\t  - [ ] Test: halt error (RATE_LIMIT) terminates loop immediately\n132\t  - [ ] Test: empty loop block (no tasks) terminates immediately\n133\t  - [ ] Test: all existing story 5-1 tests still pass (regression check is implicit)\n134\t  - [ ] Verify 80%+ coverage on loop-related code paths\n135\t\n136\t## Dev Notes\n137\t\n138\t### Module Design\n139\t\n140\tThis story modifies `workflow-engine.ts` — the same file from story 5-1. The loop execution logic is added alongside the existing sequential execution. No new files are created; this is purely additive to the existing module.\n141\t\n142\t### Integration Points\n143\t\n144\tSame as story 5-1, plus:\n145\t- `DispatchResult.output` — parsed as `EvaluatorVerdict` JSON after verify tasks\n146\t- `WorkflowState.evaluator_scores` — populated with parsed scores\n147\t- `WorkflowState.circuit_breaker.triggered` — checked each iteration to halt loop\n148\t- `WorkflowState.iteration` — incremented per loop pass\n149\t\n150\t### Data Flow\n151\t\n152\t```\n153\texecuteWorkflow(config)\n154\t  ... (sequential steps from story 5-1) ...\n155\t  \n156\t  For LoopBlock flow step:\n157\t    executeLoopBlock(loopBlock, state, config, workItems)\n158\t      while true:\n159\t        state.iteration++\n160\t        lastVerdict = null\n161\t        \n162\t        for taskName in loopBlock.loop:\n163\t          task = config.workflow.tasks[taskName]\n164\t          \n165\t          if task.scope === 'per-story':\n166\t            failedItems = lastVerdict ? getFailedItems(lastVerdict, workItems) : workItems\n167\t            for item in failedItems:\n168\t              prompt = lastVerdict ? buildRetryPrompt(item.key, lastVerdict.findings) : defaultPrompt\n169\t              state = dispatchTask(task, taskName, item.key, definition, state, config, prompt)\n170\t          \n171\t          if task.scope === 'per-run':\n172\t            state = dispatchTask(task, taskName, '__run__', definition, state, config)\n173\t            lastVerdict = parseVerdict(result.output)\n174\t            recordScore(state, lastVerdict)\n175\t        \n176\t        if lastVerdict?.verdict === 'pass' → break (success)\n177\t        if state.iteration >= maxIterations → break (max-iterations)\n178\t        if state.circuit_breaker.triggered → break (circuit-breaker)\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\t### Prompt Construction for Retry Tasks\n182\t\n183\tWhen findings are available, the retry prompt is enriched:\n184\t```\n185\tRetry story {storyKey}. Previous evaluator findings:\n186\t\n187\tAC #1 (FAIL): Description of the AC\n188\t  Evidence: Reasoning from evaluator\n189\t  \n190\tAC #3 (UNKNOWN): Description of the AC\n191\t  Evidence: Could not verify — timeout\n192\t\n193\tFocus on fixing the failed criteria above.\n194\t```\n195\t\n196\tWhen no findings are available (first iteration or parse failure), the standard prompt is used: `\"Implement story {storyKey}\"`.\n197\t\n198\t### EvaluatorVerdict Shape\n199\t\n200\tPer AD5 in architecture-v2.md:\n201\t```typescript\n202\tinterface EvaluatorVerdict {\n203\t  verdict: 'pass' | 'fail';\n204\t  score: {\n205\t    passed: number;\n206\t    failed: number;\n207\t    unknown: number;\n208\t    total: number;\n209\t  };\n210\t  findings: Array<{\n211\t    ac: number;\n212\t    description: string;\n213\t    status: 'pass' | 'fail' | 'unknown';\n214\t    evidence: {\n215\t      commands_run: string[];\n216\t      output_observed: string;\n217\t      reasoning: string;\n218\t    };\n219\t  }>;\n220\t  evaluator_trace_id: string;\n221\t  duration_seconds: number;\n222\t}\n223\t```\n224\t\n225\tThe engine does NOT validate the verdict against a JSON schema (that's the evaluator module's job in Epic 6). It simply attempts `JSON.parse()` and checks for required top-level fields.\n226\t\n227\t### dispatchTask() Modification\n228\t\n229\tThe `dispatchTask()` function needs a small modification to accept an optional custom prompt parameter, so that retry dispatches can include findings. Currently the prompt is hardcoded based on `storyKey`. The change:\n230\t\n231\t```typescript\n232\t// Before (story 5-1):\n233\texport async function dispatchTask(task, taskName, storyKey, definition, state, config)\n234\t\n235\t// After (story 5-2):\n236\texport async function dispatchTask(task, taskName, storyKey, definition, state, config, customPrompt?)\n237\t```\n238\t\n239\tWhen `customPrompt` is provided, it's used instead of the default `\"Implement story {storyKey}\"`.\n240\t\n241\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n242\t\n243\t- Does NOT implement the evaluator module — that's Epic 6. Verdict parsing here just does `JSON.parse()` on the output string\n244\t- Does NOT implement the circuit breaker module — that's Epic 7. This story only checks `state.circuit_breaker.triggered` which will be set by the circuit breaker module\n245\t- Does NOT implement crash recovery within loop blocks — that's story 5-3\n246\t- Does NOT implement the `codeharness run` CLI command — that's story 5-4\n247\t- Does NOT validate verdicts against JSON schema — that's story 6-2\n248\t- Does NOT manage Docker lifecycle — that's story 6-1\n249\t\n250\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n251\t\n252\t- **Do NOT import evaluator or circuit-breaker modules** — this story checks state fields only, no module coupling\n253\t- **Do NOT implement retry backoff** — loop iterations run immediately; rate limiting is handled by agent-dispatch\n254\t- **Do NOT implement partial score tracking across stories** — the verdict is per-run (all stories), not per-story\n255\t- **Do NOT change the sequential execution path** — only the loop block handling changes\n256\t\n257\t### Testing Strategy\n258\t\n259\tSame mocking approach as story 5-1. The `DispatchResult.output` mock returns JSON strings simulating evaluator verdicts. Tests verify:\n260\t1. Loop termination conditions (pass, max-iterations, circuit-breaker)\n261\t2. Correct prompt construction with findings\n262\t3. Failed-story-only filtering\n263\t4. Verdict parsing (success and failure)\n264\t5. Iteration tracking\n265\t6. Error propagation\n266\t\n267\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n268\t\n269\tFrom story 5-1:\n270\t- `isLoopBlock()` type guard already exists — checks for `loop` property on flow step\n271\t- `PER_RUN_SENTINEL = '__run__'` constant exists\n272\t- `HALT_ERROR_CODES` set exists for `RATE_LIMIT`, `NETWORK`, `SDK_INIT`\n273\t- `handleDispatchError()` and `recordErrorInState()` helper functions exist\n274\t- `dispatchTask()` handles trace IDs, session boundaries, source isolation — reuse as-is\n275\t- `loadWorkItems()` returns `WorkItem[]` — reuse as-is\n276\t\n277\tFrom architecture-v2.md:\n278\t- AD5: EvaluatorVerdict shape is defined (see above)\n279\t- AD1: Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine`, not a separate module\n280\t- The engine reads `circuit_breaker.triggered` from state; the circuit-breaker module (Epic 7) is responsible for setting it\n281\t\n282\t### References\n283\t\n284\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 5.2: Flow Execution — Loop Blocks]\n285\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — workflow-engine]\n286\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema]\n287\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — existing sequential execution, isLoopBlock(), dispatchTask()]\n288\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — LoopBlock, FlowStep, ResolvedTask]\n289\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState, EvaluatorScore, CircuitBreakerState]\n290\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — DispatchResult, DispatchError, DispatchOptions]\n291\t- [Source: templates/workflows/default.yaml — loop: [retry, verify]]\n292\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps.md — predecessor story]\n293\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013UbHyVXQj1k3dWQ4gFNapF","session_id":"7447df8e-50f4-441a-b8fe-e85605fee72e","uuid":"5d03100a-5a02-488a-804a-f63b9c68d755","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:17:23.969Z"}
