{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013UbHyVXQj1k3dWQ4gFNapF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 5-2 is complete. Here is the summary:\n\n**Story 5.2: Flow Execution — Loop Blocks** is implemented and marked for review.\n\n**What was done:**\n- **`src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`** — Added `EvaluatorVerdict` interface, `parseVerdict()`, `buildRetryPrompt()`, `getFailedItems()`, `executeLoopBlock()`, and internal `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. Modified `dispatchTask()` to accept optional `customPrompt`. Replaced the loop-skip logic in `executeWorkflow()` with actual loop block execution supporting three termination conditions: verdict pass, max-iterations, and circuit-breaker.\n- **`src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`** — Added 27 new tests across 4 describe blocks (`parseVerdict`, `buildRetryPrompt`, `getFailedItems`, `loop block execution`). Updated the old \"skips loop blocks\" test to verify loop execution instead.\n\n**Test results:** 66/66 tests pass in workflow-engine.test.ts. Full suite: 3990/3990 pass. Coverage on workflow-engine.ts: 95.14% statements, 86.04% branches, 100% functions.\n\n**Story file:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks.md` — Status: review\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Code duplication**: `dispatchTaskWithResult()` duplicates most of `dispatchTask()` internals. The original `dispatchTask()` does not return the `DispatchResult` object, only the updated state. Rather than refactoring the public API (which would break story 5-1 callers), I created an internal variant. This is tech debt that should be addressed — ideally `dispatchTask` should return both state and result.\n- **Conservative failed-story filtering**: `getFailedItems()` returns all items on failure because the `EvaluatorVerdict` tracks per-AC findings, not per-story results. True per-story filtering would require a verdict shape change or a mapping from ACs to stories, which is out of scope.\n- **Circuit breaker test**: The circuit breaker test relies on `writeWorkflowState` side-effecting the state object (mutating via mock). This works because the loop reads `state.circuit_breaker.triggered` from the current state reference, but it's a fragile coupling to the mock implementation.\n- **Uncovered branches** (86.04%): The remaining uncovered branches are edge cases in the loop around missing task/agent definitions within loop blocks, which are already covered by the sequential execution tests for the same pattern.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 9, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~300 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~50 lines), `npm run build` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 11 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 2 times, workflow-engine.ts read 2 times, story file read 3 times)\n- Redundant operations: Story file read 3 times (initial, checking tasks, checking end-of-file for sections) — could have read once with full content. Two separate coverage grep commands due to first returning empty."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a802f04b7c6d28198 (use SendMessage with to: 'a802f04b7c6d28198' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 86313\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 383175</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7447df8e-50f4-441a-b8fe-e85605fee72e","uuid":"5d14a8ac-7a7e-4921-8de2-22ef569b090c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:23:43.576Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your respon