{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015C13xdNBciqUayRiz2U2Ys","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7447df8e-50f4-441a-b8fe-e85605fee72e","uuid":"9c9b1c7d-631f-4dc2-8bd9-52bc158f1fe5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:32:22.337Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Redundant operations: Story file read 3 times, two separate coverage grep commands","newString":"- Redundant operations: Story file read 3 times, two separate coverage grep commands\n\n### 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks — code-review (2026-04-03T02:32)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Stale verdict bug — non-halt errors left `lastVerdict` from previous iteration intact, causing potential stale pass/findings.\n- HIGH: 80-line code duplication — `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()` identical except return type. Refactored to delegate.\n- HIGH: Uncovered branches in duplicate code eliminated by deduplication.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):**\n- `getFailedItems()` always returns all items on fail — verdict shape is per-run not per-story.\n- Circuit breaker test relies on shallow-spread mutation.\n\n**Coverage:** 96.37% stmt, 88.75% branch, 100% functions. All 158 files above 80% floor. Lines 457, 462-463, 491 remain uncovered (warn paths for missing task/agent in loop blocks).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage with file list (~30 lines), full test suite (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 14 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 5 times in chunks)\n- Redundant operations: 5 chunked reads of test file, two coverage runs","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — create-story (2026-04-03T00:25)\n\n- **Risk: `trace_ids` field on WorkflowState** — adding optional field requires updating `isValidWorkflowState()`. Made optional to avoid breaking existing states.\n- All 9 ACs are test-provable. Pure logic module with no I/O.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Glob: 3\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — dev-story (2026-04-03T00:30)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Write: 2, Bash: 4, Glob: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — code-review (2026-04-03T00:37)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `formatTracePrompt('')` silently produced empty trace marker. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor. Fixed with 10 new tests.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):** duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — verification (2026-04-03T00:55)\n\n- **`npx codeharness verify` fails** due to stale `AGENTS.md` — wants documentation for new modules in `src/lib/` (agent-dispatch.ts, agent-resolver.ts, session-manager.ts, trace-id.ts). Documentation debt, not a story 4-3 issue.\n- Build, tests (36/36), and coverage (100% trace-id.ts) all clean.\n- All 9 ACs verified with evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: test:unit run (~50 lines), trace-id verbose test (~40 lines), coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: codeharness verify called twice\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — create-story (2026-04-03T01:05)\n\n- **Risk:** AC #4 depends on `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` having `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` from story 3-2. Not verified that template exists.\n- `/tmp/` path pattern is Unix-specific. Not a concern on darwin but noted for portability.\n- All 9 ACs are test-provable (pure file system operations testable with real temp dirs).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (architecture-v2.md: 2 reads)\n- Redundant operations: Two Grep calls to `source_access` could have been one\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:10)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Read: 5, Bash: 4, Grep: 4, Write: 2, Edit: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~160 lines), full test suite (~20 lines), tsc noEmit (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — code-review (2026-04-03T01:18)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Path traversal via runId injection — unsanitized user input in file path. Fixed with `sanitizeRunId()`.\n- HIGH: Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss. Fixed with `deduplicateFilename()`.\n- MEDIUM: Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs. Fixed with pre-creation cleanup.\n- MEDIUM: Missing edge case tests for sanitization, dedup, return shape. Fixed.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):** deduplicateFilename counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage (~80 lines), git status (~30 lines), git diff (~16 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: minor — two test assertion corrections needed\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — verification (2026-04-03T01:30)\n\n- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met` flags) which are not set by manual test runs. Harness-level tracking issue, not a story defect.\n- **AGENTS.md stale:** verify command flagged `src/lib/AGENTS.md` as missing entry for `source-isolation.ts`. Documentation gap, not an AC requirement.\n- Build, tests (21 source-isolation tests, 3924 total), and coverage (100% source-isolation.ts) all clean.\n- All 9 ACs verified with evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: test:unit (~50 lines), coverage full run (~40 lines), evaluator.yaml (~22 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Coverage run twice (once default, once targeted)\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — create-story (2026-04-03T01:37)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** issues.yaml schema (FR40-41) is only sketched in AD6 — exact key format assumed without validation.\n- **Prompt construction underspecified:** minimal prompt approach used, likely needs refinement later.\n- **Loop block deferral:** AC #8 defers loop blocks to story 5-2 with skip+warn.\n- All 14 ACs are test-provable (pure orchestrator, all behavior verifiable with mocked deps).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 12, Glob: 5, Grep: 1, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:48)\n\n- **Boundary test enforcement:** Project convention requires `// IGNORE:` comments on all catch blocks. Missed on first pass, fixed after test failure.\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing TS errors unrelated to this story. Not fixed.\n- **Coverage gaps:** Lines 148-152 (null check on parsed issues YAML) and lines 316-317, 405 (edge cases in flow execution) uncovered. Defensive null checks hard to trigger through mock setup. Coverage still at 89.91%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 13, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~30 lines), full test suite (~20 lines), type check (~2 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — code-review (2026-04-03T01:55)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Coverage gaps — added 8 new tests. Coverage now 99.2% stmt / 87% branch.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):**\n- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in dispatchTask else branch\n- handleDispatchError and recordErrorInState could be merged\n- warn() calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to EngineResult.errors\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 5, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Ran coverage grep 3 times with different patterns\n\n### 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks — create-story (2026-04-03T02:13)\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- `dispatchTask()` needs backward-compatible change (adding optional `customPrompt` parameter) — could affect story 5-1's tests.\n- Verdict parsing is deliberately naive (`JSON.parse` only). Full schema validation deferred to Epic 6 (story 6-2).\n- `maxIterations` default of 5 is an assumption without a specific number in the PRD.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 10 ACs are `test-provable` — pure orchestration logic.\n- Story 5-1 left `isLoopBlock()` skip logic as a placeholder for this story.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Read: 6, Grep: 3, Glob: 3, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks — dev-story (2026-04-03T02:20)\n\n- **Code duplication**: `dispatchTaskWithResult()` duplicates most of `dispatchTask()` internals. Created internal variant rather than refactoring public API (would break 5-1 callers). Tech debt.\n- **Conservative failed-story filtering**: `getFailedItems()` returns all items on failure because `EvaluatorVerdict` tracks per-AC findings, not per-story results.\n- **Circuit breaker test fragility**: Test relies on `writeWorkflowState` side-effecting the state object via mock — fragile coupling.\n- **Uncovered branches** (86.04%): Edge cases in loop around missing task/agent definitions within loop blocks.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 9, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~300 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~50 lines), `npm run build` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 11 total reads (story file read 3 times)\n- Redundant operations: Story file read 3 times, two separate coverage grep commands\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":177,"oldLines":3,"newStart":177,"newLines":23,"lines":[" - Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~300 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~50 lines), `npm run build` (~5 lines)"," - Files read: 8 unique, 11 total reads (story file read 3 times)"," - Redundant operations: Story file read 3 times, two separate coverage grep commands","+","+### 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks — code-review (2026-04-03T02:32)","+","+**Bugs found and fixed:**","+- HIGH: Stale verdict bug — non-halt errors left `lastVerdict` from previous iteration intact, causing potential stale pass/findings.","+- HIGH: 80-line code duplication — `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()` identical except return type. Refactored to delegate.","+- HIGH: Uncovered branches in duplicate code eliminated by deduplication.","+","+**LOW (not fixed):**","+- `getFailedItems()` always returns all items on fail — verdict shape is per-run not per-story.","+- Circuit breaker test relies on shallow-spread mutation.","+","+**Coverage:** 96.37% stmt, 88.75% branch, 100% functions. All 158 files above 80% floor. Lines 457, 462-463, 491 remain uncovered (warn paths for missing task/agent in loop blocks).","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 21","+- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: coverage with file list (~30 lines), full test suite (~15 lines)","+- Files read: 8 unique, 14 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 5 times in chunks)","+- Redundant operations: 5 chunked reads of test file, two coverage runs"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
